Attributions

NexusRT builds on the following hardware, software, and research artifacts.
Their authors retain all original rights; this notice acknowledges influence
and provides a starting point for downstream users.

1. NVIDIA CUDA Driver API, CUDA Runtime, GPUDirect Storage, GPUDirect RDMA,
   Tensor Memory Accelerator (TMA), Inline Compression (ILC), Thread Block
   Clusters / Distributed Shared Memory.
     Copyright (c) NVIDIA Corporation.
     Licensed under NVIDIA Software License terms where applicable.
     https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/

2. Apple Metal Framework, Metal Performance Shaders, MLX.
     Copyright (c) Apple Inc.
     https://developer.apple.com/metal/

3. DREAM: Device-Driven Efficient Access to Virtual Memory
     Agarwal et al., ACM (2025).
     https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/3721145.3725748

4. KOKARYOKU — Bare-metal GPU platform research.
     arXiv:2604.13600v1

5. TrainMover: An Interruption-Resilient Runtime for ML Training.
     arXiv:2412.12636

6. The research paper "Beyond the OS: A Firmware-Centric Runtime for
   End-to-End Acceleration of LLM Pipelines on NVIDIA GPUs", which
   motivates this implementation.
